SR 20 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 20 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 20(By Senators Oliverio, Garcia, Smith (Mr. President), Taylor, Clements, Rose, and Jeffries)[Introduced March 4, 2025] Designating March 5, 2025, as West Virginia University Day at the Legislature.Whereas, West Virginia University is the state’s first and largest land-grant university, which has been dedicated to serving the citizens of West Virginia for more than 155 years; andWhereas, West Virginia University offers students the perks and programs of a major research institution at a great value; andWhereas, West Virginia University offers more than 340 majors at the bachelor’s, master’s, doctoral, and professional levels to help students discover their passion and fulfill their purpose; andWhereas, West Virginia University Extension serves as the primary outreach arm of West Virginia University with an office in each of the state’s 55 counties, where agents and specialists deliver trusted research and innovative solutions to improve the lives and livelihoods of all West Virginians in the areas of youth development, agriculture and natural resources, community engagement, health and nutrition, and family and community development; and Whereas, West Virginia University Extension experts aid West Virginians in building economic prosperity through career exploration, financial literacy, workforce development, and occupational safety training opportunities for 21st century jobs; andWhereas, West Virginia University Extension strives to equip the next generation with leadership, critical thinking, and entrepreneurial skills through youth education and outreach programs, such as Energy Express, Career Readiness, STEM, and West Virginia’s state 4-H – the largest youth organization in the state, which reaches more than 67,000 youths; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby designates March 5, 2025, as West Virginia University Day at the Legislature; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the President of West Virginia University E. Gordon Gee, and to West Virginia University Extension. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


