ach of the state’s 55 counties, where agents and specialists deliver trusted research and innovative solutions to improve the lives and livelihoods of all West Virginians in the areas of youth development, agriculture and natural resources, community engagement, health and nutrition, and family and community development; and Whereas, West Virginia University Extension experts aid West Virginians in building economic prosperity through career exploration, financial literacy, workforce development, and occupational safety training opportunities for 21st century jobs; andWhereas, West Virginia University Extension strives to equip the next generation with leadership, critical thinking, and entrepreneurial skills through youth education and outreach programs, such as Energy Express, Career Readiness, STEM, and West Virginia’s state 4-H – the largest youth organization in the state, which reaches more than 67,000 youths; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby designates March 5, 2025, as West Virginia University Day at the Legislature; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the President of West Virginia University E. Gordon Gee, and to West Virginia University Extension. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: